# Git and Versioning Release Rule

- Use feature branches for all work; avoid direct commits to `main`.
- Before merging to `main`, ensure tests and build pass locally.
- Keep commits focused and descriptive; explain intent in commit body.
- Open a PR (or equivalent review step) before merging to `main`.

## Version bump requirement

- On every merge/push to `main`, increment app version in:
  - `site/src/config/appVersion.ts`
- Follow semantic progression:
  - patch: `1.0` -> `1.0.1` for fixes
  - minor: `1.0.1` -> `1.1.0` for features
  - major: `1.1.0` -> `2.0.0` for breaking changes
- Include the version bump in the same release commit/PR so deployed UI always shows the correct version.
